"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. One of the secrets I found out about in this last year of gardening is something that's helped me out so much. I was going to mosquito suits and all sorts of other things. Here in Houston, Texas, we have a vicious mosquito issue. And uh that's okay, that's life. Uh we live in a hot human environment, so like things that are active are gonna live here, and mosquitoes are gonna take advantage of that. But this past year I found out about geraniums. This is a citronella geranium down here, and I'm beginning to wind it up this thing. And the trick is you come over here and you kind of swim in a little bit, and you you rub the oils that this produce all over you. I just did on my arm, but I'll do it all over the place. A lot of these uh branches move up and down, they're great for it. And afterwards, you'll just wreak a citronella, like this beautiful lemony citrus. Oh, it's wonderful. Smells great, and you'll smell of it pretty good. And when you do smell of it, the mosquitoes just leave you alone. And so the first thing you do when you walk in is you wash in the geranium, the citronella, and then you walk around, do your business and get it on, you know, you're working here. After about 10-15 minutes, you don't smell as much. You go back there and you refresh because you're just rubbing at it, uh spreading some of the oils from it, and you do this until you go inside and you never get bit. It actually works, but you gotta stay fresh with it, you gotta use a lot of the oils, you gotta kind of get a big plant and work it. So, what I'm doing is I'm gonna put this stuff everywhere because I don't like mosquitoes, and I've done a bunch of clones, but maybe right behind me, you can see a bunch of those clones are now potted plants. I'm gonna line the property with these so that you can swim in geraniums everywhere you go. Anyway, thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.64,\n      